entry.string: Because the file #(1) is present and writable, it is being used as the fallback mechanism for logging purposes.
There exists a fallback mechanism which will log to file #(1) even if the logging is turned off, so admins can still log if unable to install/use the logconfig module.
For this fallback mechanism to work, it is necessary for this file to exist and be writable by the http server user.
